1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,360
(Six years ago)

3
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:37,800
We met at the Sen Bar.

4
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:39,281
I walked up to her

5
00:01:39,281 --> 00:01:40,761
and asked her for her number.

6
00:01:40,921 --> 00:01:41,880
You know what she said?

7
00:01:42,281 --> 00:01:44,320
She said, "Are you trying to hit on me?"

8
00:01:44,561 --> 00:01:46,600
It means, 'Are you trying to hit on me?'

9
00:01:48,401 --> 00:01:50,001
I thought she was mad.

10
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:51,960
So I said, "Sorry."

11
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,401
And then you know what? I walked away.

12
00:01:55,401 --> 00:01:57,921
I said, "No, no, no. Come back.

13
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,320
Finish your words."

14
00:02:10,081 --> 00:02:11,401
Cheers.

15
00:02:17,801 --> 00:02:19,241
What do you think of her?

16
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,681
She's really cute.

17
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,040
- Cute?
- Cute.

18
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:25,241
You mean she's not good?

19
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,281
Barry, give her a score?

20
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,001
Six point five.

21
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:32,160
That's not bad.

22
00:02:32,561 --> 00:02:33,561
One hundred in total.

23
00:02:40,584 --> 00:02:41,401
What did you say?

24
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:45,961
It was about Barry's new job.

25
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,401
He'll be transferred to China division
as General Manager.

26
00:02:49,841 --> 00:02:50,801
Congratulations!

27
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,121
Thank you.

28
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,760
It's a huge opportunity for me
and a big challenge.

29
00:02:57,681 --> 00:02:58,961
China is a big market for us.

30
00:02:59,241 --> 00:03:00,480
And a lot of beautiful ladies.

31
00:03:00,961 --> 00:03:01,640
Yeah.

32
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:05,121
Actually, it's a very tough market.
Not very easy.

33
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,281
Yeah, I know. It's difficult.

34
00:03:08,561 --> 00:03:12,281
There's some senior staff over there
who are experts in GST much more than me.

35
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,121
Plus, I'm a foreigner, you know.

36
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,760
So it's indeed gonna be tough
to manage them.

37
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:20,001
Frankly, I am a little bit worried.

38
00:03:20,001 --> 00:03:21,200
They'll eat you.

39
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:24,081
Yeah, yeah.
Frankly, I am a little bit worried.

40
00:03:24,961 --> 00:03:27,681
You should go with your...
You know, someone.

41
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,401
Buddy. Friend.

42
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:33,040
Could be human resources.

43
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,081
Yeah, you're right.

44
00:03:34,081 --> 00:03:35,200
I've thought about that.

45
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:40,200
I need someone who's an expert
in human resources. A China expert.

46
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:44,440
And most importantly, someone
who'll be willing to follow my lead.

47
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,281
How about a woman?

48
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:47,841
A woman?

49
00:03:59,361 --> 00:04:02,720
You're the Human Resources Director
of Chiprise?

50
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:03,320
Yeah.

51
00:04:03,961 --> 00:04:05,160
This company is huge.

52
00:04:05,801 --> 00:04:08,720
- How come you never told me about that?
- I didn't know. Just knew.

53
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,320
Not only Chiprise.

54
00:04:12,081 --> 00:04:17,361
I'm the HR consultant
at Filly Consulting and Vast Consulting.

55
00:04:17,361 --> 00:04:21,361
Plus, I have 15 years
of international HR experience.

56
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:25,921
More importantly, I'm Chinese.

57
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,960
I know how to run in China.

58
00:04:31,001 --> 00:04:32,520
You want to come with me to China?

59
00:04:32,721 --> 00:04:35,320
For you, it's "come to China".

60
00:04:36,801 --> 00:04:41,601
But for me, it's going home.

61
00:04:43,601 --> 00:04:44,001
Alright.

62
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:47,721
Let's go to your home.

63
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,161
Yep.

64
00:04:53,481 --> 00:04:54,376
Let's celebrate!

65
00:04:54,664 --> 00:04:55,921
Cheers!

66
00:05:11,784 --> 00:05:18,376
(Awakening, Steel Rose,
Flexibility Defeats Strength)

67
00:05:18,376 --> 00:05:21,837
=Episode 23=
(Steel Rose)

68
00:05:37,001 --> 00:05:37,640
Xiao.

69
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:39,624
You're here.

70
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:45,041
What's it?

71
00:05:45,041 --> 00:05:45,520
Come on in.

72
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,080
My capacity's been bad
since the surgery.

73
00:05:55,681 --> 00:05:56,361
You two talk.

74
00:05:56,561 --> 00:05:57,544
I'll go to the restroom.

75
00:06:04,561 --> 00:06:05,561
I heard.

76
00:06:06,921 --> 00:06:10,681
I heard you fell asleep
in the storage room earlier.

77
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,361
Why'd you sleep there?

78
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:16,361
I didn't mean to sleep there.

79
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,400
I just...

80
00:06:21,512 --> 00:06:24,440
I haven't slept for days.

81
00:06:25,561 --> 00:06:27,400
I took some medication.

82
00:06:28,161 --> 00:06:30,121
I suddenly got drowsy this morning.

83
00:06:30,121 --> 00:06:33,520
So I thought maybe I could take a nap
there for 20 minutes.

84
00:06:34,001 --> 00:06:35,601
And I even set an alarm.

85
00:06:36,121 --> 00:06:39,481
My alarm... it didn't go off.

86
00:06:39,601 --> 00:06:42,721
No. Well, my alarm...

87
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:46,801
It did go off, but I turned it off.

88
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,001
Hailun, listen to me.

89
00:06:49,001 --> 00:06:50,440
You're severely sleep-deprived.

90
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:54,320
Well, I'll talk to Xiao Yang
about reducing your workload.

91
00:06:54,481 --> 00:06:55,640
So you can rest well, okay?

92
00:06:55,681 --> 00:06:57,760
No, no. I don't need less workload.

93
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,041
It's not the workload.

94
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,400
Mr. Li, I want to go back.

95
00:07:04,681 --> 00:07:06,001
Please let me go back.

96
00:07:06,001 --> 00:07:07,840
Let... let me go back.

97
00:07:08,561 --> 00:07:10,161
Please, let me go back.

98
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,840
Let me go back.

99
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:13,361
Hailun.

100
00:07:13,481 --> 00:07:14,840
I'm begging you, let me go back.

101
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:15,801
Calm down.

102
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,320
Hailun,

103
00:07:18,681 --> 00:07:19,801
I know you want to be back.

104
00:07:22,121 --> 00:07:23,361
But you really can't.

105
00:07:24,721 --> 00:07:27,361
It's a decision
finalized by HR and Finance.

106
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,880
It's a done deal.

107
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:33,001
Let's think it through carefully.

108
00:07:34,601 --> 00:07:36,721
We can definitely find another way.

109
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:38,504
There'll be another way.

110
00:07:42,561 --> 00:07:46,640
By the way, the company
is arranging overseas rotations.

111
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,520
Do you want to go to Singapore?

112
00:07:51,041 --> 00:07:54,001
S-S-Singapore?

113
00:07:56,241 --> 00:07:56,921
Singapore.

114
00:07:57,601 --> 00:07:59,601
Singapore's abundant sunshine
is good for you.

115
00:08:00,361 --> 00:08:02,320
You get a change of scenery.

116
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:07,361
And having overseas rotation experience
makes promotion easier.

117
00:08:16,681 --> 00:08:17,681
Can I go?

118
00:08:19,161 --> 00:08:21,840
If you want to go, I'll arrange it.

119
00:08:32,321 --> 00:08:33,160
You're exhausted.

120
00:08:34,121 --> 00:08:35,081
You need to rest.

121
00:08:40,241 --> 00:08:41,321
Go home and get some sleep.

122
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,121
(I heard Su Li will rotate
to Singapore next year.)

123
00:08:59,481 --> 00:09:00,760
(Yeah, three people in total.)

124
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,800
(Two men and one woman.)

125
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:02,841
(I didn't even know.)

126
00:09:02,841 --> 00:09:04,880
(I would've applied if I'd known.)

127
00:09:05,361 --> 00:09:06,160
(Don't be silly.)

128
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,241
(Applying won't get you
such an opportunity.)

129
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,640
(They're all boss-appointed.)

130
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:10,800
(True.)

131
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:13,640
(Who's going to Singapore?)

132
00:09:14,601 --> 00:09:15,280
(Su Li.)

133
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,640
(One from Zhang Jianyue's team.)

134
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,864
(And Cao Lei from your team.)

135
00:09:18,601 --> 00:09:20,841
(Oh, you're not
on Li Dongming's team anymore.)

136
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,568
(Mr. Li)

137
00:09:34,081 --> 00:09:36,721
Sorry. The number you have dialed
is powered off.

138
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,601
You can't go in.

139
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,081
Mr. Fan, I couldn't stop her.

140
00:10:15,201 --> 00:10:15,721
Mr. Fan.

141
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,241
It's fine. You can go.

142
00:10:18,601 --> 00:10:20,400
Mr. Fan. Mr. Fan.

143
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:22,040
Mr. Fan, I need to tell you something.

144
00:10:23,441 --> 00:10:24,121
You are?

145
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:25,841
I'm Qiao Hailun.

146
00:10:26,721 --> 00:10:27,201
Have a seat.

147
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:30,800
Mr. Fan, I need to tell you something.

148
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,321
I'll leave after I tell you.

149
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:43,201
Li Dongming and I
have been having an affair.

150
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:45,280
At first, we were good.

151
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,841
He said he liked me too.

152
00:10:48,961 --> 00:10:54,121
Then suddenly, he transferred me
from his team to Xiao Yang's team.

153
00:10:54,841 --> 00:10:58,400
I know...
I know this is just his scheme.

154
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:02,441
He wants...
He wants to force me out of Ruijin.

155
00:11:03,081 --> 00:11:04,920
I just want to do my job well.

156
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:09,001
I can't leave. I really can't leave.

157
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:13,800
If I leave, I'll never find another job.

158
00:11:15,001 --> 00:11:17,640
Mr. Fan, I begged him.

159
00:11:18,441 --> 00:11:21,920
I told him I wanted back on his team.

160
00:11:22,961 --> 00:11:25,680
But... But he absolutely refused.

161
00:11:26,841 --> 00:11:27,961
He lied to me again.

162
00:11:27,961 --> 00:11:28,760
He lied to me again.

163
00:11:29,441 --> 00:11:32,520
He lied, saying he'd arrange for me
to work in Singapore.

164
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:33,640
No.

165
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:36,840
He didn't lie to you.

166
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:39,920
You'll be going to Singapore
on rotation next month.

167
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:46,280
The list for Singapore
was finalized last month.

168
00:11:46,601 --> 00:11:49,201
I know the names. I'm not on it.

169
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,001
That list was for last month.

170
00:11:51,441 --> 00:11:52,392
You're up this month.

171
00:11:52,601 --> 00:11:53,841
You're not in their batch.

172
00:11:54,841 --> 00:11:57,241
By the way, what's your current level?

173
00:12:01,961 --> 00:12:02,640
Level 5.

174
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:03,920
Then you are now Level 6.

175
00:12:07,121 --> 00:12:08,001
Level 6?

176
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:12,081
Why?

177
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,201
Because of your outstanding work,
of course.

178
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:15,760
You've earned it.

179
00:12:20,841 --> 00:12:21,680
Is that possible?

180
00:12:23,321 --> 00:12:24,280
Why wouldn't it be?

181
00:12:25,361 --> 00:12:26,680
I'm the CEO of Ruijin.

182
00:12:27,481 --> 00:12:28,481
Would I lie to you?

183
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,680
HR will come to see you in half an hour.

184
00:12:45,961 --> 00:12:46,481
Mr. Fan.

185
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:47,640
Dongming.

186
00:12:48,361 --> 00:12:50,001
What is it? Calling me out at this hour.

187
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:51,441
Why not at the office tomorrow?

188
00:12:54,241 --> 00:12:56,280
Office talk is for the office.

189
00:12:57,201 --> 00:12:58,800
The other talk is for here.

190
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:04,201
Dongming, you've made quite a mess.

191
00:13:05,721 --> 00:13:07,201
If I hadn't stepped in today,

192
00:13:07,481 --> 00:13:10,601
Qiao Hailun
would have shouted it everywhere.

193
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:20,121
Right, I didn't expect it
to blow up like this.

194
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,081
I just handled it.

195
00:13:29,672 --> 00:13:33,426
(Non-Disclosure Agreement)

196
00:13:43,601 --> 00:13:44,680
I made her shut up.

197
00:13:45,224 --> 00:13:47,102
(Non-Disclosure Agreement)

198
00:13:50,961 --> 00:13:52,361
Read the contract carefully.

199
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,760
Let me state this again.

200
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:03,121
You cannot, in any form,

201
00:14:03,321 --> 00:14:05,601
make or publish any unfavorable
or derogatory remarks

202
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:10,121
about the company, its employees,
or any of its business partners.

203
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:15,001
The Level 6 promotion email
will soon arrive in your inbox.

204
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,040
You can apply for your Singapore visa.

205
00:14:17,321 --> 00:14:18,880
Admin will assist you.

206
00:14:25,241 --> 00:14:28,081
Mr. Fan, I...

207
00:14:29,601 --> 00:14:31,640
I really don't know what to say.

208
00:14:33,001 --> 00:14:36,601
Thank you. I owe you a huge favor.

209
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:39,081
No, don't owe me that.

210
00:14:40,601 --> 00:14:41,680
I have more to say.

211
00:14:42,081 --> 00:14:42,640
Go ahead.

212
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:47,081
Every company
has its own revered culture and spirit.

213
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,441
The old chairman always believed

214
00:14:49,841 --> 00:14:53,760
that family harmony is essential
for creating a successful entrepreneur.

215
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:59,560
The company has never violated
this principle when selecting leaders.

216
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:05,241
So I want you to withdraw
from the CEO election.

217
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:13,321
So this is what you really want.

218
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:14,920
I know

219
00:15:15,721 --> 00:15:17,760
if we compete, I stand no chance.

220
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:21,640
Two-thirds of the senior partners
are on good terms with you.

221
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,640
But you and I
have been on good terms too.

222
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:28,560
If you don't run, no one can rival me.

223
00:15:30,001 --> 00:15:32,201
I've been looking for a chance
to discuss it with you.

224
00:15:33,321 --> 00:15:35,400
Well, here's the chance.

225
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,081
Alright, I agree.

226
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:48,880
Thank you.

227
00:15:50,321 --> 00:15:54,560
I've had our Singapore branch
arrange a position for Qiao Hailun.

228
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,241
She can leave by early next month
at the latest.

229
00:15:59,001 --> 00:16:01,040
Thank you, Mr. Fan. I appreciate it.

230
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,920
What brings you here, Mr. Li?

231
00:16:17,441 --> 00:16:18,481
I want a deal with you.

232
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,400
Want to take down Barry?

233
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:22,441
What do you mean?

234
00:16:23,441 --> 00:16:24,441
Do you want to or not?

235
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:27,920
Go on.

236
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,920
For our deals with GST,

237
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,920
20% of the quoted prices are kickbacks.

238
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:34,481
Barry and Fan split that money.

239
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,121
I have all the accounts and evidence.

240
00:16:37,481 --> 00:16:39,920
If you do this, Fan will go down.

241
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,241
Then let him go down.

242
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,601
Did he offend you?

243
00:16:44,201 --> 00:16:46,160
I want to run for the next CEO.

244
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:47,640
Fan won't step aside.

245
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:49,800
See?

246
00:16:50,321 --> 00:16:52,560
You missed your chance
to be the CEO's wife.

247
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:58,441
Just say it. What do you want from me?

248
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:03,400
Give me all the evidence
you have on me and Qiao Hailun.

249
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:08,001
Deal.

250
00:17:17,441 --> 00:17:19,401
(Li Dongming getting dirt on Barry)

251
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:20,481
(makes sense.)

252
00:17:20,921 --> 00:17:22,800
(Because Li Dongming
is Barry's supplier.)

253
00:17:23,401 --> 00:17:24,441
(But Zeng Zixuan?)

254
00:17:24,881 --> 00:17:26,760
(She's just a junior specialist
in Promotions.)

255
00:17:26,921 --> 00:17:28,241
(What's her dirt on Barry?)

256
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,600
(And so logically presented)

257
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:31,600
(with a complete chain.)

258
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:33,760
(Only one possibility.)

259
00:17:34,481 --> 00:17:35,721
(Someone's backing her.)

260
00:17:36,481 --> 00:17:38,201
(Someone inside GST)

261
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:39,520
(and in management.)

262
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:41,280
(Who?)

263
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,161
(It can't be Peter.)

264
00:17:43,481 --> 00:17:45,241
(This wouldn't benefit him.)

265
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,001
(That leaves only one person.)

266
00:17:54,241 --> 00:17:54,721
What?

267
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,120
You seem different today.

268
00:17:59,921 --> 00:18:00,600
In your demeanor.

269
00:18:02,401 --> 00:18:03,280
An unemployed drifter?

270
00:18:08,241 --> 00:18:09,881
I'll return to my hometown
in a few days.

271
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:11,144
To see my parents.

272
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,736
When will you return?

273
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:16,481
Not decided.

274
00:18:16,921 --> 00:18:19,201
Are you thinking of leaving Guangzhou

275
00:18:19,481 --> 00:18:21,001
and quitting the corporate world?

276
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,441
Corporate world?

277
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:24,481
It's treacherous.

278
00:18:24,721 --> 00:18:27,641
I'm afraid if I stay, I'll sink deeper.

279
00:18:29,161 --> 00:18:31,840
What did you do to sink deep?

280
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:38,600
Xu left over sexual harassment.

281
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:41,241
I set that up.

282
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,201
Tommy's persuading that girl.

283
00:18:46,201 --> 00:18:48,001
Now it's up to her courage
to make the toast.

284
00:18:48,441 --> 00:18:52,800
You need to bravely charge
towards the boss.

285
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:55,560
You mean that night at Cocoon Club,

286
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:58,280
you told Zeng Zixuan to make that toast?

287
00:18:58,441 --> 00:18:59,560
I didn't tell her to toast.

288
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:02,280
But in a place like that,
it was either Zeng Zixuan or Li Zixuan.

289
00:19:03,441 --> 00:19:06,241
Finding a woman to toast Xu wasn't hard.

290
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:11,881
How could you be so awful?

291
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,161
Look how much you've hurt me!

292
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,201
I was wrong.

293
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:26,840
A few days ago,
Zeng Zixuan tore into me.

294
00:19:28,441 --> 00:19:28,840
Why?

295
00:19:29,161 --> 00:19:31,721
She said I treat the underlings
like pawns.

296
00:19:32,241 --> 00:19:34,001
On the surface, it's for everyone.

297
00:19:34,001 --> 00:19:35,441
But actually, it's all for myself.

298
00:19:36,481 --> 00:19:37,360
I thought about it.

299
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:38,840
She's not wrong.

300
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:40,760
What? You want to quit too?

301
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,560
Just to walk away?

302
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:45,384
Thought about it.

303
00:19:46,881 --> 00:19:48,201
I thought about it many times.

304
00:19:50,481 --> 00:19:51,600
But I can't bear to leave.

305
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,881
Zeng Zixuan says she's an underling.

306
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:58,001
Who isn't?

307
00:19:58,161 --> 00:19:59,560
I'm an underling too.

308
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:02,641
You know, in this company,
the underlings do the work,

309
00:20:02,641 --> 00:20:04,040
sell the liquor,

310
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:05,560
and even take the blame.

311
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:08,241
We underlings have done so much.

312
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:10,520
I've struggled so hard
to climb up just a little bit.

313
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:12,001
Am I supposed to quit over a dog?

314
00:20:12,001 --> 00:20:13,080
Why on earth would I?

315
00:20:14,401 --> 00:20:16,520
Let me tell you,
once I become Sales Director,

316
00:20:16,961 --> 00:20:18,560
I'm pulling those girls up with me.

317
00:20:19,241 --> 00:20:21,401
I'm going to make
my Promotions Department shine.

318
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,800
Never expected you
to have that ruffian streak.

319
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:26,560
Here, I toast you.

320
00:20:29,641 --> 00:20:30,120
By the way,

321
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:34,681
the other day, I found a presentation
on Zeng Zixuan's computer.

322
00:20:35,481 --> 00:20:37,040
It was to report Barry to headquarters.

323
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,040
And it was bilingual.

324
00:20:40,641 --> 00:20:42,520
Someone must be behind Zeng Zixuan.

325
00:20:44,641 --> 00:20:45,560
And a powerful one.

326
00:20:57,520 --> 00:21:00,320
(I have to admit Zhao Mei is more suited
for this position than I am.)

327
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,241
(Women are always more resilient.)

328
00:21:03,961 --> 00:21:05,800
(And I believe
with Zhao Mei's shrewdness,)

329
00:21:06,241 --> 00:21:08,481
(she'll find that one behind it all
very quickly.)

330
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,840
(But that's her problem.)

331
00:21:11,481 --> 00:21:13,040
(I'm an outsider now.)

332
00:21:14,241 --> 00:21:16,080
(And when I completely
let go of all this,)

333
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:16,961
(I suddenly realized)

334
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,641
(how distant all those things felt.)

335
00:21:20,441 --> 00:21:22,120
(Promotions? Climbing the ladder?)

336
00:21:22,241 --> 00:21:24,201
(Underlings? Higher-ups?)

337
00:21:25,201 --> 00:21:26,560
(None of those mattered anymore.)

338
00:21:46,641 --> 00:21:48,001
Why must you see me today?

339
00:21:48,241 --> 00:21:49,280
I have meetings all day.

340
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,760
I don't want Zeng Zixuan.

341
00:21:52,161 --> 00:21:52,681
What?

342
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,921
Her work attitude is problematic.

343
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:58,441
I don't think
she's fit to stay on my team.

344
00:21:58,881 --> 00:21:59,961
You cannot fire her.

345
00:22:01,241 --> 00:22:01,921
Why not?

346
00:22:02,641 --> 00:22:04,161
She's still on probation.

347
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,481
She was brought back by the company.

348
00:22:08,401 --> 00:22:09,800
Although put in your department,

349
00:22:10,641 --> 00:22:14,201
she represents the company's
zero tolerance for workplace misconduct

350
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:19,080
and the company's determination
to clean up the workplace atmosphere.

351
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:22,881
So her presence is symbolic.

352
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,560
It's not about what she actually does.

353
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:32,360
Ms. Qi, you mean for me
to treat Zeng Zixuan like a mascot?

354
00:22:33,881 --> 00:22:36,360
I mean,
you have no authority to fire her.

355
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:39,800
Understood.

356
00:22:44,641 --> 00:22:47,481
So you're the one
behind Zeng Zixuan, right?

357
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:52,241
I don't know what you mean.

358
00:22:54,681 --> 00:22:55,161
Okay.

359
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:12,641
She guessed it was me.

360
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:16,320
Shouldn't we speed things up?

361
00:23:17,481 --> 00:23:18,600
To avoid complications.

362
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:23,961
Thank you.

363
00:23:25,201 --> 00:23:28,520
(Yes, I am the mastermind
trying to bring down Barry.)

364
00:23:29,161 --> 00:23:29,800
(I know)

365
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:33,840
(people talk behind my back that Barry's
the emperor and I'm the empress.)

366
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:35,600
(What can I say?)

367
00:23:36,441 --> 00:23:37,441
(Frogs in a well.)

368
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:41,320
(How could I possibly
respect that idiot Barry?)

369
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:45,760
(The only reason I volunteered
to help him conquer China)

370
00:23:46,201 --> 00:23:48,721
(was because
I saw the opportunity in it.)

371
00:23:50,001 --> 00:23:51,161
(I knew full well)

372
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:55,441
(Five years ago)
(a Chinese HR professional abroad)

373
00:23:55,721 --> 00:23:57,921
(faced an extremely narrow path upward.)

374
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:03,280
(To advance further,
I had to return to my own soil.)

375
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,241
(Yes, Barry looks down on me.)

376
00:24:06,961 --> 00:24:09,401
(The GST old-timers
don't take me seriously, either.)

377
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,320
(So what?)

378
00:24:12,481 --> 00:24:14,961
(Arrogance always backfires.)

379
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:18,881
(I just want to focus on doing
what I set out to do)

380
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:22,760
(and achieving my goals.
That's all that matters.)

381
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:25,080
Over there is Shen Mo, as I mentioned,

382
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:27,881
GST China's largest distributor.

383
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:29,401
Let's go toast him.

384
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:30,881
Hold on, Barry.

385
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,280
He's very influential,

386
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:34,721
but we're the brand.

387
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:37,241
Shouldn't he come over to toast Barry?

388
00:24:38,241 --> 00:24:38,921
You're right.

389
00:24:39,441 --> 00:24:41,961
I'll make the introduction.
I'll go get him.

390
00:24:42,201 --> 00:24:44,600
Peter, you're the Sales VP.

391
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,520
Shouldn't this be handled by a director?

392
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:50,161
Mr. Xu,

393
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:53,641
please ask Mr. Shen to come over

394
00:24:53,641 --> 00:24:54,881
and toast Barry.

395
00:25:00,441 --> 00:25:01,681
Sure, why not?

396
00:25:02,856 --> 00:25:03,624
I'll go with you.

397
00:25:07,001 --> 00:25:07,520
Let's drink.

398
00:25:39,641 --> 00:25:40,560
- Hi.
- Hi.

399
00:25:40,921 --> 00:25:42,201
Nice to meet you, Barry.

400
00:25:42,401 --> 00:25:44,560
Nice to meet you. Cheers.

401
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:46,001
Cheers.

402
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,080
Mr. Xu.

403
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:54,696
You wanted to see me?

404
00:25:57,608 --> 00:26:00,080
(A few months ago)

405
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:02,921
I just spoke to Xu Yuntian
about an extra three thousand cases.

406
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:04,921
He didn't agree.

407
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:07,161
Did he outright say he disagreed?

408
00:26:07,681 --> 00:26:08,808
He said he couldn't do it,

409
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:12,201
and my request
was like killing the goose...

410
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:14,312
Killing the goose
that lays the golden eggs.

411
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,201
Right.

412
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:19,241
Didn't you tell him you're doing this

413
00:26:19,241 --> 00:26:20,881
because you need reelection leverage?

414
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:22,320
I hinted at it to him.

415
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:24,241
But he simply didn't care.

416
00:26:26,401 --> 00:26:27,241
I understand him.

417
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:28,201
What?

418
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:31,800
You're the 6th China division president
he's served.

419
00:26:32,201 --> 00:26:33,800
Whether it's you or someone else,

420
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,600
it makes no difference to him.

421
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,560
He only cares about his own position.

422
00:26:38,961 --> 00:26:39,961
He'd rather offend you

423
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:42,001
than apply pressure downward.

424
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:46,320
In that case, let's replace him
with someone who'll toe the line.

425
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:49,721
I'm leaving the task to you.

426
00:26:59,401 --> 00:27:01,641
(I let Barry and Xu Yuntian
fight each other.)

427
00:27:02,401 --> 00:27:03,641
(Once Xu Yuntian fell,)

428
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,560
(Barry could be easily taken out.)

429
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,800
(I just need to pick the right person)

430
00:27:08,241 --> 00:27:09,441
(and the right timing)

431
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:10,840
(to push everything forward.)

432
00:27:12,760 --> 00:27:14,040
(Barry gave me a 6.5 rating.)

433
00:27:15,481 --> 00:27:16,840
(What gave him the right?)

434
00:27:18,721 --> 00:27:19,641
(In this world,)

435
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,921
(who has the right to rate anyone?)

436
00:27:23,161 --> 00:27:26,040
(I define who I am.)

437
00:27:26,481 --> 00:27:27,240
It's on Weibo too.

438
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,360
Should we take action?

439
00:27:29,641 --> 00:27:30,320
No rush.

440
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:34,641
Let's see how things unfold.

441
00:27:35,401 --> 00:27:39,161
This might blow over
in a couple of days.

442
00:27:39,840 --> 00:27:43,721
After all, Xu Yuntian isn't a celebrity.

443
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:48,161
If we make a big PR push,

444
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,600
it'll only draw more attention.

445
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:53,001
Yes.

446
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:55,520
Don't act rashly.

447
00:27:57,161 --> 00:27:57,921
Keep in touch.

448
00:27:58,961 --> 00:27:59,481
Bye.

449
00:28:01,401 --> 00:28:02,161
(What can I say?)

450
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:05,080
(Human desires always climb higher.)

451
00:28:05,961 --> 00:28:08,641
(When I realized I was GST's)

452
00:28:08,641 --> 00:28:12,681
(first female HR VP in all these years,)

453
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:16,840
(my ambitions soared.)

454
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:19,432
(Barry seeks reappointment)

455
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,161
(to keep profiting in China.)

456
00:28:21,881 --> 00:28:24,681
(While I'm aiming to replace him)

457
00:28:26,161 --> 00:28:29,800
(as GST China's first female president.)

458
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:34,721
We have a chance
to remove the Sales Director.

459
00:28:39,624 --> 00:28:40,560
Didn't you say Tuesday?

460
00:28:41,001 --> 00:28:41,800
Why the delay?

461
00:28:43,001 --> 00:28:46,320
I wanted to give you extra time
to scout the job market.

462
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,120
What job market?

463
00:28:48,721 --> 00:28:50,001
The reemployment scene.

464
00:28:50,721 --> 00:28:52,001
I'm sure you've spent these days

465
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:54,921
visiting every possible employer.

466
00:28:56,721 --> 00:28:58,161
The reemployment market

467
00:28:58,520 --> 00:29:02,481
is equally brutal for 35-year-old women

468
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,520
and 50-year-old men.

469
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:07,441
Cut the crap.

470
00:29:10,241 --> 00:29:10,920
Three million.

471
00:29:11,681 --> 00:29:13,001
My contributions to the company

472
00:29:13,641 --> 00:29:14,441
earn me that.

473
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:17,401
I haven't seen your contributions,

474
00:29:18,201 --> 00:29:20,800
but the company's contributions to you
are obvious.

475
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:25,120
I hear you've amassed quite a fortune.

476
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:27,481
Multiple properties alone.

477
00:29:32,560 --> 00:29:33,641
May I ask,

478
00:29:35,201 --> 00:29:36,161
what's it to you?

479
00:29:38,441 --> 00:29:40,080
Of course it's none of my business.

480
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:42,641
It's not coming from my pocket.

481
00:29:44,241 --> 00:29:46,080
Let's be frank.

482
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:49,040
You hold damaging information
about the company.

483
00:29:49,681 --> 00:29:51,080
If it leaks,

484
00:29:51,481 --> 00:29:52,800
the company faces huge trouble.

485
00:29:53,161 --> 00:29:54,401
But that's not my business.

486
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:59,201
I have compromising material on you.

487
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:02,120
If released,

488
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:04,040
you'll face severe consequences.

489
00:30:04,560 --> 00:30:05,961
You could land in jail instantly.

490
00:30:09,520 --> 00:30:10,360
What do you want?

491
00:30:11,241 --> 00:30:11,881
Simple.

492
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:16,401
Compile everything you have
and hand it to me.

493
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:21,520
Times, locations, people, and events.
All clearly documented.

494
00:30:22,401 --> 00:30:26,681
I'll give you three million in severance
on behalf of the company in return.

495
00:30:27,481 --> 00:30:30,001
Clean and clear. Deal?

496
00:30:40,001 --> 00:30:40,641
Qi Youlan,

497
00:30:41,201 --> 00:30:44,001
that's the most absurd thing
you've ever said to me.

498
00:30:45,201 --> 00:30:46,320
Are you insane, or am I?

499
00:30:47,001 --> 00:30:49,241
You're asking me to incriminate myself?

500
00:30:52,961 --> 00:30:54,001
You think I'm crazy?

501
00:30:54,280 --> 00:30:55,161
Xu Yuntian,

502
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:59,040
why can't you break your old habits?

503
00:31:00,001 --> 00:31:01,161
In a big company like GST,

504
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:04,241
can you possibly be involved
in every single matter?

505
00:31:05,241 --> 00:31:08,080
Can't you find some things
unrelated to you to share?

506
00:31:08,241 --> 00:31:09,481
Must I spell it out?

507
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:14,840
Who are you targeting?

508
00:31:24,241 --> 00:31:24,760
(Yes.)

509
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:27,921
(The person behind Zeng Zixuan
is Qi Youlan.)

510
00:31:28,681 --> 00:31:30,320
(She wants to take Barry down.)

511
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:32,441
(My gut tells me)

512
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:34,800
(the Sales Director position
is available again.)

513
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,560
(Should I seize it?)

514
00:31:37,641 --> 00:31:38,681
(But after all this time,)

515
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:41,360
(why did I want
to be Sales Director again?)

516
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,080
I heard you want to be Sales Director.

517
00:31:48,961 --> 00:31:50,040
I'll back you always.

518
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:53,080
I even thought that if I never found
my own purpose in life,

519
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,641
I'd make following you my goal.

520
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:57,201
You treat everyone under you as a pawn.

521
00:31:57,721 --> 00:31:59,600
When you need them, you sweet-talk them.

522
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,672
When you don't, you kick them aside.

523
00:32:01,961 --> 00:32:02,961
And Fang.

524
00:32:03,201 --> 00:32:05,241
Didn't you claim to be close to her?

525
00:32:05,681 --> 00:32:07,360
You didn't even visit her once.

526
00:32:08,401 --> 00:32:09,881
Hao took the blame for you.

527
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:12,120
He said he did it voluntarily.

528
00:32:12,441 --> 00:32:14,080
But he was just being used by you.

529
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:17,600
(I know where my loyalty lies.)

530
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:20,681
(If I want to speak up for the girls,)

531
00:32:21,001 --> 00:32:24,360
(I first need the power
to speak for them.)

532
00:32:53,201 --> 00:32:54,681
Are you settling in okay here?

533
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:58,120
If you can't find a suitable place,
just stay here.

534
00:32:59,001 --> 00:33:00,161
It's nice to have company.

535
00:33:01,120 --> 00:33:02,320
That's too much trouble.

536
00:33:04,481 --> 00:33:06,921
I heard sales targets
might not be met this year?

537
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:09,401
Because Shen Mo
refused the channel stuffing?

538
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:13,641
Yes. Barry's anxious
to meet with Shen Mo.

539
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:16,161
He won't be anxious for much longer.

540
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:18,441
Once you release that presentation,

541
00:33:18,881 --> 00:33:20,241
he'll be finished on the spot.

542
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:24,481
But something tells me
the evidence still isn't solid enough.

543
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:27,881
You listed so much,
and you still think it's not enough?

544
00:33:28,961 --> 00:33:33,320
I feel it lacks the definitive proof
that seals the deal.

545
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:39,001
I'm telling you,
Zhao Mei saw that presentation.

546
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:41,600
Her? How did she see it?

547
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:43,496
She saw Zeng Zixuan's computer.

548
00:33:43,641 --> 00:33:44,921
An IT tech showed her.

549
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:47,161
I never expected

550
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:51,760
that she'd have so many friends at GST.

551
00:33:52,241 --> 00:33:52,921
It's true.

552
00:33:53,681 --> 00:33:54,600
I underestimated her.

553
00:33:56,961 --> 00:33:58,161
What do you want for dinner?

554
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:00,520
Whatever you say.

555
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:05,800
I'll order whatever.

556
00:34:08,361 --> 00:34:10,921
Is Barry the one
you're trying to take down?

557
00:34:11,680 --> 00:34:12,761
That presentation

558
00:34:12,761 --> 00:34:16,841
shows collusion between Barry,
Xu Yuntian, and Shen Mo.

559
00:34:17,680 --> 00:34:21,120
But the sales department actually
has been playing this game for years.

560
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:24,640
Besides, for next year's China sales,

561
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:27,160
HQ might not want
to rock the boat right now.

562
00:34:27,761 --> 00:34:30,321
So if you really want
to bring Barry down,

563
00:34:31,281 --> 00:34:33,040
you should focus on something else.

564
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:35,200
Do you have a better way?

565
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:39,401
I have stronger evidence here.

566
00:34:39,801 --> 00:34:43,120
For our deals with GST,
20% of the quoted prices are kickbacks.

567
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:45,680
Barry and Fan split that money.

568
00:34:45,841 --> 00:34:47,441
I have all the accounts and evidence.

569
00:34:47,441 --> 00:34:49,556
(Evidence on kickbacks, chat history,
Qiao, Shanghai)

570
00:35:12,401 --> 00:35:14,040
What are you... No!

571
00:35:14,801 --> 00:35:15,801
You can't do this!

572
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:18,361
You can't do this! No!

573
00:35:22,761 --> 00:35:25,001
(Justice will prevail)
(A key executive at a major foreign firm)

574
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:27,640
(Bribery feels good, jail feels worse)
(was detained in a major bribery case,)

575
00:35:27,841 --> 00:35:29,281
(Top corporate scandal of the year)
(causing a stir industry-wide.)

576
00:35:29,881 --> 00:35:31,961
(This isn't a bribe, it's career suicide)
(This case might lead to a chain reaction)

577
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:35,040
(New character to the jailhouse drama)
(involving multiple firms and employees.)

578
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,600
I just think it's strange.

579
00:35:37,001 --> 00:35:39,080
Why would Li Dongming
give you all this evidence?

580
00:35:43,881 --> 00:35:44,841
We're getting divorced.

581
00:35:45,921 --> 00:35:48,560
The evidence
was one of our divorce terms.

582
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:03,481
Zhao Mei, you're back.

583
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:04,520
Off work?

584
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:05,481
What brings you here?

585
00:36:06,560 --> 00:36:07,680
We've been here a while.

586
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:09,881
Still working so late, huh?

587
00:36:09,881 --> 00:36:11,001
It's too hard.

588
00:36:14,761 --> 00:36:16,961
Look, you've lost weight again.

589
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:18,001
Been busy lately.

590
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:20,481
Right? You need
to take care of yourself.

591
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:24,680
Health is your
most important asset, right?

592
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:32,001
Zhao Mei,

593
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:34,720
Dongming told us everything.

594
00:36:34,720 --> 00:36:36,321
He did make a mistake.

595
00:36:37,481 --> 00:36:41,001
His job has too many temptations,

596
00:36:41,441 --> 00:36:42,921
with lots of young women around.

597
00:36:43,881 --> 00:36:46,401
So it was inevitable he'd slip up.

598
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:48,080
You're in the liquor business.

599
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:50,240
You should understand him, right?

600
00:36:50,240 --> 00:36:52,281
Stop it. Don't say that.

601
00:36:53,361 --> 00:36:53,961
Zhao Mei,

602
00:36:54,881 --> 00:36:56,321
we came here today

603
00:36:56,961 --> 00:37:00,520
to make our position clear.

604
00:37:00,841 --> 00:37:02,961
First, regarding this matter,

605
00:37:03,321 --> 00:37:05,841
your wishes come first, absolutely.

606
00:37:06,481 --> 00:37:08,040
That's beyond doubt.

607
00:37:09,120 --> 00:37:15,040
Second, as Dongming's father,
I must apologize to you.

608
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:19,801
Poor parenting is the father's fault.

609
00:37:19,801 --> 00:37:22,921
Dad, please don't say that.

610
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:23,881
It's only right.

611
00:37:25,921 --> 00:37:28,640
Thirdly, marriage isn't easy.

612
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:32,120
You two married later in life.

613
00:37:32,921 --> 00:37:34,921
I believe when you two got married,

614
00:37:34,921 --> 00:37:37,640
it must have been after careful thought.

615
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:41,401
Now you're facing some difficulties.

616
00:37:42,401 --> 00:37:43,120
So look,

617
00:37:44,001 --> 00:37:47,040
could you hold off
on rushing to divorce?

618
00:37:48,441 --> 00:37:52,441
Calm down
and see if there's another solution.

619
00:37:52,841 --> 00:37:53,640
Exactly.

620
00:37:54,080 --> 00:37:56,761
Zhao Mei, think it over carefully again.

621
00:37:56,961 --> 00:37:58,560
This is a major life decision.

622
00:37:58,680 --> 00:38:02,001
There might be a better way
to resolve this.

623
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:03,640
About this matter,

624
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:08,361
I had a very serious talk with Dongming.

625
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:12,040
He deeply regrets what he did.

626
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:13,680
He told me

627
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:17,640
if he gets a chance to stay with you,

628
00:38:18,321 --> 00:38:20,441
he'll sincerely turn over a new leaf

629
00:38:20,761 --> 00:38:21,961
and reform himself.

630
00:38:22,401 --> 00:38:23,361
He'll never do it again.

631
00:38:23,761 --> 00:38:25,441
I believe he's sincere.

632
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:27,680
He even cried.

633
00:38:28,080 --> 00:38:31,401
Yes. Dongming is in a lot of pain.

634
00:38:31,401 --> 00:38:33,200
I've never seen him like that before.

635
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:35,080
You know Dongming.

636
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:37,481
He's been a kind boy
since he was little.

637
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:39,720
His nature is good, right?

638
00:38:39,881 --> 00:38:42,040
And you two fell in love freely.

639
00:38:42,281 --> 00:38:43,520
You should understand him.

640
00:38:43,961 --> 00:38:45,441
Please forgive him.

641
00:38:45,961 --> 00:38:46,560
Mom.

642
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:46,961
You...

643
00:38:47,401 --> 00:38:47,801
Dad.

644
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:49,881
Zhao Mei,

645
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,481
don't give an answer yet.

646
00:38:52,801 --> 00:38:56,801
I suggest you two talk again.

647
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:58,801
Have a deep conversation

648
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:01,120
and give each other a chance.

649
00:39:16,361 --> 00:39:18,761
Right, there's soup
simmering on the stove.

650
00:39:18,961 --> 00:39:19,720
Have some.

651
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:21,401
Zhao Mei,

652
00:39:21,881 --> 00:39:23,441
you saved my life.

653
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:26,560
I truly can't bear to lose you.

654
00:39:27,520 --> 00:39:31,080
Think it over again.
Give Dongming a chance.

655
00:39:32,281 --> 00:39:33,240
Think about it.

656
00:39:33,761 --> 00:39:34,568
The elevator's here.

657
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:43,001
Dad, Mom, I've made my decision.

658
00:39:44,441 --> 00:39:46,160
And I've prepared the divorce papers.

659
00:39:48,841 --> 00:39:49,520
Take care.

660
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:03,464
Hello.

661
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:05,881
Li Dongming, you're something else,

662
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:07,961
bringing your parents into this.

663
00:40:08,921 --> 00:40:10,680
When will you sign the divorce papers?

664
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:12,160
Why drag this out?

665
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:15,321
Come to my office tomorrow.

666
00:40:17,801 --> 00:40:18,761
(I'm in Singapore now.)

667
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:20,240
(Feeling relieved?)

668
00:40:21,001 --> 00:40:22,640
(Think you've won?)

669
00:40:23,481 --> 00:40:25,080
(You're wrong. You didn't win.)

670
00:40:25,640 --> 00:40:27,361
(He didn't send me away for you.)

671
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:28,761
(It was for himself.)

672
00:40:29,361 --> 00:40:30,761
(He was afraid if I kept pushing,)

673
00:40:30,921 --> 00:40:32,600
(he'd be the one to go.)

674
00:40:32,961 --> 00:40:34,001
(He's such a coward.)

675
00:40:34,441 --> 00:40:36,200
(I was fooled by a coward for so long.)

676
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:38,481
(You know what?
You're worse off than me.)

677
00:40:38,961 --> 00:40:40,441
(I was fooled by him for a while.)

678
00:40:40,441 --> 00:40:42,801
(But you? You've been fooled
for half your life.)

679
00:40:43,520 --> 00:40:46,080
(Do you know what he did outside?)

680
00:40:46,841 --> 00:40:51,001
(By the way, do you want to know
how he described you to me?)

681
00:40:51,841 --> 00:40:54,560
(It would make you furious if you knew.)

682
00:40:56,136 --> 00:40:56,872
(Where are you?)

683
00:40:57,481 --> 00:40:58,720
(At your community gate.)

684
00:41:10,602 --> 00:41:15,342
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

685
00:41:19,792 --> 00:41:21,712
♪Too much of shame♪

686
00:41:22,058 --> 00:41:24,854
♪To waste it crying♪

687
00:41:27,312 --> 00:41:29,232
♪Leave all behind you♪

688
00:41:29,232 --> 00:41:31,512
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

689
00:41:31,632 --> 00:41:33,861
♪You know how far you've gone♪

690
00:41:33,996 --> 00:41:36,272
♪In the fire you rise again♪

691
00:41:36,458 --> 00:41:38,818
♪You made it through the worst♪

692
00:41:38,956 --> 00:41:41,160
♪The best is yet to come♪

693
00:41:41,403 --> 00:41:43,543
♪The best is yet to come♪

694
00:41:46,245 --> 00:41:47,568
♪Isn't it magical♪

695
00:41:47,568 --> 00:41:49,200
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

696
00:41:49,232 --> 00:41:51,699
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

697
00:41:51,699 --> 00:41:54,152
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

698
00:41:54,233 --> 00:41:56,881
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

699
00:41:56,970 --> 00:41:59,501
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

700
00:41:59,581 --> 00:42:01,803
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

701
00:42:01,945 --> 00:42:03,026
♪But I don't want to♪

702
00:42:03,135 --> 00:42:05,401
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

703
00:42:05,517 --> 00:42:06,582
♪Until 3 AM♪

704
00:42:06,753 --> 00:42:07,958
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

705
00:42:08,112 --> 00:42:09,345
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

706
00:42:09,436 --> 00:42:11,800
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

707
00:42:11,947 --> 00:42:16,357
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

708
00:42:31,082 --> 00:42:32,518
♪Leave all behind you♪

709
00:42:32,622 --> 00:42:35,109
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

710
00:42:35,292 --> 00:42:37,421
♪You know how far you've gone♪

711
00:42:37,608 --> 00:42:39,948
♪In the fire you rise again♪

712
00:42:40,016 --> 00:42:42,282
♪You made it through the worst♪

713
00:42:42,642 --> 00:42:44,720
♪The best is yet to come♪

714
00:42:44,969 --> 00:42:47,139
♪The best is yet to come♪

715
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:50,992
♪Isn't it magical♪

716
00:42:50,992 --> 00:42:54,638
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

717
00:42:54,672 --> 00:42:56,528
♪And I see them sparkling♪

718
00:42:56,752 --> 00:42:58,883
♪Nobody knows♪

719
00:42:59,504 --> 00:43:01,414
♪What tomorrow brings♪

720
00:43:01,680 --> 00:43:04,003
♪You made it through the worst♪

721
00:43:04,190 --> 00:43:06,398
♪The best is yet to come♪

722
00:43:06,685 --> 00:43:08,834
♪The best is yet to come♪

723
00:43:09,130 --> 00:43:10,544
♪Isn't it magical♪

724
00:43:10,544 --> 00:43:12,756
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

725
00:43:12,830 --> 00:43:15,184
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

726
00:43:15,184 --> 00:43:16,272
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

727
00:43:16,272 --> 00:43:19,723
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

728
00:43:20,176 --> 00:43:22,450
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

729
00:43:22,864 --> 00:43:23,728
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

730
00:43:23,728 --> 00:43:25,248
♪Isn't it magical♪
